<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 3:20PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A cluster of strong thunderstorms will impact portions of
Scotland, southeastern Richmond and southwestern Hoke Counties
through 400 PM EDT...
At 319 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurinburg, moving southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Rockingham, Hamlet, Maxton, Antioch, Dobbins Heights,
Wagram, Gibson, East Laurinburg and Laurel Hill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
